   "source": [
    "# 🏋️ Gym Members Exercise & Health Data Analysis\n",
    "### Google Data Analytics Capstone — Style Project\n",
    "**Dataset:** [Gym Members Exercise Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/valakhorasani/gym-members-exercise-dataset) — Kaggle  \n",
    "**Tools:** Python · Pandas · NumPy · Matplotlib · Seaborn  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## About This Project\n",
    "\n",
    "This project follows the **6-step data analysis framework** used in the Google Data Analytics Certificate:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Ask → Prepare → Process → Analyze → Share → Act**\n",
    "\n",
    "We analyze gym members' exercise and health data to uncover patterns in workout behavior, calorie burn, fitness levels, and BMI — and provide data-driven recommendations to help a fitness app company improve member engagement and product features.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cf6f417c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📌 Step 1: Ask\n",
    "\n",
    "### Business Task\n",
    "\n",
    "A fictional fitness app company called **FitTrack** wants to understand how people exercise and what factors affect their health outcomes. They want answers to the following questions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. What workout types are most popular among members?\n",
    "2. How does workout frequency relate to calories burned?\n",
    "3. Is there a difference in fitness levels between male and female members?\n",
    "4. What is the distribution of BMI among gym members?\n",
    "5. How does experience level affect workout performance?\n",
    "\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3e3d0ead",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Step 2: Prepare\n",
    "\n",
    "### About the Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Source:** [Kaggle — Gym Members Exercise Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/valakhorasani/gym-members-exercise-dataset)\n",
    "- **File:** `gym_members_exercise_tracking.csv`\n",
    "- **Size:** 973 rows × 15 columns\n",
    "- **License:** Public / Open\n",
    "\n",
    "### Dataset Columns\n",
    "\n",
    "| Column | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Age | Age of the member |\n",
    "| Gender | Male / Female |\n",
    "| Weight (kg) | Body weight |\n",
    "| Height (m) | Height in meters |\n",
    "| Max_BPM | Maximum heart rate during workout |\n",
    "| Avg_BPM | Average heart rate during workout |\n",
    "| Resting_BPM | Resting heart rate |\n",
    "| Session_Duration (hours) | Duration of workout session |\n",
    "| Calories_Burned | Calories burned per session |\n",
    "| Workout_Type | Type of workout (Cardio, Strength, Yoga, HIIT) |\n",
    "| Fat_Percentage | Body fat percentage |\n",
    "| Water_Intake (liters) | Daily water intake |\n",
    "| Workout_Frequency (days/week) | How many days per week they work out |\n",
    "| Experience_Level | 1 = Beginner, 2 = Intermediate, 3 = Expert |\n",
    "| BMI | Body Mass Index |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Data Credibility (ROCCC Check)\n",
    "\n",
    "| Criteria | Assessment |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **R**eliable | ✅ Structured, consistent format |\n",
    "| **O**riginal | ⚠️ Synthetic/simulated dataset from Kaggle |\n",
    "| **C**omprehensive | ✅ Covers activity, health, and demographic data |\n",
    "| **C**urrent | ✅ Recently published on Kaggle |\n",
    "| **C**ited | ✅ Publicly available with documentation |\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⚠️ **Note:** This is a simulated dataset. Results should be treated as practice analysis, not real-world findings.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29f611dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Load Libraries and Import Data"
   ]
  },
  {
